%I A394682 #19 Apr 16 2026 22:25:48
%S A394682 2,101,114797,3071673482,1955102250552194,29613643147768044223881
%N A394682 Number of order-convex subsets of the cubic grid poset [n]^3 with componentwise partial order.
%C A394682 A subset S of [n]^3 = {1,...,n}^3 with componentwise order is order-convex if whenever a, b in S with a <= c <= b, then c in S.
%C A394682 The growth rate log a(n) = Theta(n^2) is for all d >= 2 (the dimension law); the exponent 2 = d-1 for d=3 detects the spacetime dimension.
%C A394682 The 2-dimensional analog (square grid) is A393665.
%D A394682 B. Barnette, W. Nichols, and T. Richmond, The number of convex sets in a product of totally ordered sets, Rocky Mountain J. Math., 49 (2019), no. 2, 369-385.
%H A394682 Thomas DiFiore, <a href="https://github.com/tomdif/causal-algebraic-geometry-lean">Lean 4 formal verification</a>.
%H A394682 Thomas DiFiore, <a href="https://zenodo.org/records/19271767">Order-Convex Subsets of Grid Posets</a>, Zenodo.
%H A394682 B. Barnette, W. Nichols, and T. Richmond, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1216/RMJ-2019-49-2-369">The number of convex sets in a product of totally ordered sets</a>, Rocky Mountain J. Math. 49(2): 369-385 (2019).
%F A394682 a(m+n) >= a(m)*a(n) for all m, n >= 1 (supermultiplicativity).
%F A394682 a(n) <= C(2*n,n)^4 (ideal/filter injection).
%F A394682 log a(n) = Theta(n^2) (dimension law for d=3). The growth constant c_3 = lim log(a(n))/n^2 is conjectured to equal 16*log(2)/7 = 1.5842... based on c_2/c_3 = 7/4 to 4 significant figures (where c_2 = log(16) is the growth constant for d=2, A393665).
%e A394682 a(1) = 2: the empty set and {(1,1,1)}.
%e A394682 a(2) = 101: the order-convex subsets of the 8-element Boolean lattice [2]^3.
%Y A394682 Cf. A393665 (2-dimensional analog).
%K A394682 nonn,more
%O A394682 1,1
%A A394682 _Thomas DiFiore_, Mar 28 2026
